  "body": "- **I'm submitting a ...**\r\n\r\n  - [x] Feature request\r\n  - [ ] Bug report\r\n\r\n- **Feature Report**\r\n\r\nLightstreams network is a full-compatible ethereum network and therefore network clients expect to be using the same exact private keys they are using for ethereum network. \r\n\r\nAt the minute Lightstreams network is using the same path (`m/44'/60'/0'/0`) for every hw, but according the the MEW implementation there are two exceptions:\r\n- Ledger should be `m/44'/60'/0'`\r\n- Keepkey should be `m/44'/60'`\r\n\r\nPlease update Ledger and Keepkey paths to match the one used by ethereum.",
